        <briefdescription>
<para>\par \b Module Contract\/ \:</para>
<para>\par \b Purpose\/ \:  Define the ParsedDocument schema — the top-level API response model aggregating document content, metadata, attachments, warnings, and version info. </para>
        </briefdescription>
        <detaileddescription>
<para>\par \b Scope\/ \:  Root API response model — full document parsing result. \par \b Input\/ \:  None (standalone model, references DocumentContent, DocumentMetadata, self for attachments). \par \b Output\/ \:  Pydantic BaseModel <computeroutput>ParsedDocument</computeroutput> with content, metadata, version, warnings, attachments. \par \b Links\/ \:  [USES_API(7): pydantic.BaseModel; READS_DATA_FROM(8): DocumentContent, DocumentMetadata] \par \b Invariants\/ \:</para>
<para><itemizedlist>
<listitem><para>content is always present (may have empty tables and root-only structure).</para>
</listitem><listitem><para>attachments list may be empty if with_attachments=False.</para>
</listitem><listitem><para>version matches <ref refid="namespacededoc_1_1version_1a5dc678a536891bbad415bb6983ccb495" kindref="member">dedoc.version.__version__</ref>. \par \b Rationale\/ \:</para>
</listitem></itemizedlist>
</para>
<para>Q: Why self-referential for attachments? A: Attached files are parsed into ParsedDocument themselves, forming a recursive structure that matches the nested nature of document attachments. \par \b Changes\/ \:</para>
<para>LAST_CHANGE: [v1.0.0 – Initial creation with semantic markup] \par \b Module Map\/ \:</para>
<para>CLASS 10[Top-level API response — content + metadata + attachments] =&gt; ParsedDocument \par \b Use Cases\/ \:</para>
<para><itemizedlist>
<listitem><para>[ParsedDocument]: ApiEndpoint =&gt; SerializeParsingResult =&gt; ReturnJSONToClient </para>
</listitem></itemizedlist>
</para>
        </detaileddescription>
